   arguments, an explicit implementation of the vanishing discount factor
   approach to analyzing infinite-horizon Markov decision processes, and
   ideas from the theory of random walks and queues, significantly
   extending the methodology and applicability of a novel framework for
   analyzing inventory models with large lead times recently introduced by
   Goldberg and coauthors in the context of lost-sales models with positive
   lead times.
